Turkiye Halk Bankasi Seeks $500 Million Loan to Refinance Debt

-- B y   S t e p h e n   M o r r i s
-- 
2011-05-27T16:13:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-27/turkiye-halk-bankasi-seeks-500-million-loan-to-refinance-debt.html
Turkiye Halk Bankasi AS (HALKB) , a Turkish
state-run bank, began talks with banks to raise as much as $500
million of loans to refinance its existing debt.  The one-year term loans will be split between euro and
dollar tranches and will pay interest of 60 basis points over
benchmark rates, according to Bloomberg data. Lenders will get
an additional 50 basis points of fees.  A basis point is 0.01 percentage point.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Morris in  London  at 
 smorris39@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Faris Khan at 
 fkhan33@bloomberg.net . 